- "blossomed into high-energy stars" refers to animals with a high activity level more than 50% of the time;
- "special dietary needs" refers to animals that require special diets;
- "adopted before" means the animal has been adopted at least once;
- "ample space" means the kennel has more than 5 available spaces.

- 'intake types' refer to the different ways animals are brought into the shelter, such as stray, surrendered, or transferred;
- 'active staff' are those currently employed and engaged in the shelter's operations;
- 'active animal types' are the categories of animals that the shelter currently accepts or manages.
